---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import { SITE_NAME } from "../consts";
import SectionIcon from "../components/SectionIcon.astro";
import IconGridSection from "../components/sections/IconGridSection.astro";
---

<Base title={`${SITE_NAME} for Institutions`}>
	<section class="hero">
		<img
			class="image-block"
			src="/images/institutions.webp"
			alt="Institutions sharing knowledge with the public"
			loading="lazy"
			decoding="async"
			width="1155"
			height="895"
		/>
		<div>
			<h1>Institutional publishing, built for the web.</h1>
			<p class="lede">
				Libraries, universities, public organizations, and publishers—bring collections to the
				open web with trusted reading at scale.
			</p>
			<p>ReaderPub is the missing web layer: fast onboarding, clean discovery, and a real in-browser reading experience.</p>
			<div class="cta-row">
				<a class="button" href="/contact?topic=institution">Start institutional onboarding</a>
				<a class="button secondary" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section institutions-publisher-intro institutions-tight-section section-continue-next">
			<h2>Publish on the web without losing control. Keep your audience.</h2>
			<p>Launch catalogs, excerpts, and controlled reading programs on a public platform built for discovery — with secure, account-based access and a delivery model designed to reduce file leakage risk.</p>
			<p>Access is fully configurable: institutions define who can read, which content is restricted, and how access is granted across users and teams.</p>
			<ul class="bullets">
				<li>Control access by channel, cohort, or program.</li>
				<li>Deliver web-only reading through verified user accounts — no downloadable files, no heavy DRM.</li>
				<li>Track engagement across titles in real time.</li>
				<li>Showcase frontlist and backlist with confidence.</li>
				<li>Offer public excerpts or restricted access by segment.</li>
				<li>Measure engagement and demand by title.</li>
				<li>Build direct relationships with readers and partner institutions.</li>
				<li>Run collaborative reading programs with shared, pass-forward annotations across cohorts.</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="institutions-publisher-note">
				In addition to web publishing, ReaderPub delivers a production-ready EPUB that you can
				archive, distribute externally, or publish on other platforms — while keeping your primary
				access securely managed online.
			</p>
	</section>

	<IconGridSection class="institutions-tight-section section-continuation section-continue-next">
		<div class="card-grid icon-grid institutions-pair-grid">
			<div class="card icon-grid-card">
				<SectionIcon type="sale" title="Sell and rent titles" />
				<div class="icon-grid-card-copy">
					<h2>Sell and rent titles with lower fees — and keep your audience.</h2>
					<ul class="bullets">
						<li>Commerce-ready distribution: sales + rentals.</li>
						<li>Low 5% commission on sales and rentals.</li>
						<li>First-party analytics: revenue, rentals, cohorts, engagement.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
				<div class="card icon-grid-card">
					<SectionIcon type="fan" title="Add fan clubs" />
					<div class="icon-grid-card-copy">
						<h2>Add fan clubs to drive repeat demand across authors and series.</h2>
					<ul class="bullets">
						<li>Book- and author-level memberships with direct reader access.</li>
						<li>Campaign-ready drops: releases, excerpts, limited access, rentals.</li>
						<li>Community analytics connected to sales and rentals.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</IconGridSection>

	<IconGridSection class="institutions-tight-section section-continuation section-continue-next">
		<div class="card-grid icon-grid institutions-pair-grid">
			<div class="card icon-grid-card">
				<SectionIcon type="library" title="Libraries" />
				<div class="icon-grid-card-copy">
					<h2>Libraries extend their mission into the public web.</h2>
					<p>Create digital reading rooms that serve patrons, partners, and communities.</p>
					<ul class="bullets">
						<li>Extend collections with digital programs and access..</li>
						<li>Run reading programs with impact.</li>
						<li>Curate shelves and programs with public visibility.</li>
						<li>Support community reading initiatives and cohorts.</li>
						<li>Extend collections with modern web access.</li>
						<li>Track engagement to guide programming.</li>
						<li>Enable inclusive access with built-in device TTS for patrons who prefer listening.</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="institutions-outcome-note">Turn community collections into a public reading library online.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="card icon-grid-card">
				<SectionIcon type="university" title="Universities" />
				<div class="icon-grid-card-copy">
					<h2>Universities publish research with visibility and trust.</h2>
					<p>Support faculty, labs, and students with a public research library.</p>
					<ul class="bullets">
						<li>Power coursework and cohort reading.</li>
						<li>Unify campus libraries and labs.</li>
						<li>Release working papers, reports, and open archives.</li>
						<li>Power coursework reading and cohort programs.</li>
						<li>Unify campus libraries and departmental collections.</li>
						<li>Highlight institutional expertise to the public.</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="institutions-outcome-note">Publish research libraries with clear public access and attribution.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</IconGridSection>

	<IconGridSection class="institutions-tight-section section-continuation section-continue-next">
		<div class="card-grid icon-grid institutions-pair-grid">
			<div class="card icon-grid-card">
				<SectionIcon type="government" title="Government" />
				<div class="icon-grid-card-copy">
					<h2>Government publishes with transparency and reach.</h2>
					<p>Make public documents, research, and policy libraries easy to find and read.</p>
					<ul class="bullets">
						<li>Improve transparency and access.</li>
						<li>Serve staff and constituents together.</li>
						<li>Centralize reports, regulations, and public resources.</li>
						<li>Serve staff and constituents with the same library.</li>
						<li>Improve transparency with accessible reading formats.</li>
						<li>Track public engagement to inform policy work.</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="institutions-outcome-note">Make policy libraries readable and searchable for the public.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="card icon-grid-card">
				<SectionIcon type="charity" title="Public organizations" />
				<div class="icon-grid-card-copy">
					<h2>Public organizations amplify mission-driven knowledge.</h2>
					<p>Publish reports, guides, and resources that reach the right communities.</p>
					<ul class="bullets">
						<li>Share mission resources with clarity and permanence.</li>
						<li>Curate resources for communities and partners.</li>
						<li>Publish reports with lasting visibility.</li>
						<li>Curate collections for partners and constituents.</li>
						<li>Launch public reading programs and campaigns.</li>
						<li>Build trust with transparent, accessible publishing.</li>
					</ul>
					<p class="institutions-outcome-note">Deliver mission resources through a trusted public reading library.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</IconGridSection>

	<IconGridSection class="institutions-tight-section section-continuation">
		<div class="card-grid icon-grid institutions-pair-grid">
			<div class="card icon-grid-card">
				<SectionIcon type="access" title="Control access at every level" />
				<div class="icon-grid-card-copy">
					<h2>Control access at every level</h2>
					<p>
						ReaderPub gives institutions administrative control over publications, users, and teams — allowing you to manage access, roles, and distribution policies from a single platform.
					</p>
					<ul class="bullets">
						<li>Assign access by user, group, or role</li>
						<li>Control visibility of individual publications</li>
						<li>Manage internal teams and external audiences</li>
						<li>Maintain oversight across your entire catalog</li>
					</ul>
					<a class="button secondary" href="/security#control-who-reads">Learn how access control works</a>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="card icon-grid-card">
				<SectionIcon type="security" title="Built to reduce file leakage" />
				<div class="icon-grid-card-copy">
					<h2>Built to reduce file leakage</h2>
					<p>
						In file-based systems, content can circulate beyond the platform after delivery. ReaderPub minimizes that risk by keeping primary reading access on the web instead of routinely distributing a complete downloadable book file.
					</p>
					<p class="institutions-leakage-note">
						Traditional DRM tries to control a file after delivery. ReaderPub reduces risk earlier by avoiding routine end-user delivery of the primary reading file.
					</p>
					<a class="button secondary" href="/security">Read about our protection model</a>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</IconGridSection>

	<section class="footer-cta institutions-onboarding-cta section-continuation">
		<h2>Onboard your organization on ReaderPub</h2>
		<p class="lede">Tell us what you need: We’ll set up your onboarding.</p>
		<div class="cta-row institutions-onboarding-cta-row">
			<a class="button" href="/contact">Institutional onboarding</a>
			<a class="button secondary" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
		</div>
	</section>

	<style>
		:global(.institutions-tight-section.section-continuation) {
			padding-top: 0 !important;
		}

		:global(.institutions-tight-section.section-continuation > .card-grid) {
			margin-top: 0 !important;
		}

		:global(.institutions-tight-section.section-continuation.section-continue-next) {
			padding-bottom: var(--section-flow-gap) !important;
		}

		.institutions-pair-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
			width: 100%;
		}

		.institutions-publisher-note {
			color: var(--accent);
		}

		.institutions-leakage-note {
			color: var(--text) !important;
		}

		.institutions-outcome-note {
			color: var(--accent) !important;
			font-size: 18px !important;
		}

		.institutions-onboarding-cta {
			width: 100%;
			max-width: none;
			text-align: center;
			padding: 29px 32px !important;
		}

		.institutions-onboarding-cta-row {
			justify-content: center !important;
			width: 100%;
		}

		@media (max-width: 980px) {
			.institutions-pair-grid {
				grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			}
		}
	</style>
</Base>
